The No. 229 ranked prospect out of Fort Lauderdale, Florida chose the Dawgs over Miami, Auburn and Oklahoma among others. Georgia lost a commitment from running back John Emery in October and now replace that spot with McIntosh. The Dawgs now have 13 ESPN 300 commitments in the No. 4 ranked recruiting class.</p></div><div class="now-feed_item-meta display-share" data-src="http://www.espn.com/espn/now?nowId=21-41043935-4" data-original-src="http://www.espn.com/espn/now?nowId=21-41043935-4">

He particularly praised Syracuse quarterback Eric Dungey.
"I think Eric Dungey is a very competitive, very, very tough guy at the quarterback position," Pasqualoni said. "And like every program, every football program in America, you need a good quarterback at this level and at that level, the Division I level, to win. And I think Eric Dungey gives them that and hope that they can be successful throughout the season."</p></div><div class="now-feed_item-meta display-share" data-src="http://www.espn.com/espn/now?nowId=21-41043848-4" data-original-src="http://www.espn.com/espn/now?nowId=21-41043848-4">
